-- | Roles & onboarding for the Syndicate facility.
--
-- This module defines the parties that participate in a facility and the on-ledger
-- authorization that lets the Agent-Bank Co-Pilot (a separate Daml party) act on a
-- need-to-know basis. Parties themselves are plain `Party` values; authority is granted
-- explicitly through contracts so the *ledger* — never a prompt — is the guardrail.
module Syndicate.Roles where

-- | The five logical roles in a syndicated facility. These are convenience aliases over
-- `Party`; they carry no authority on their own — authority comes from being a signatory
-- or controller of a contract.
type Borrower  = Party
type AgentBank = Party
type Lender    = Party
-- | The LLM co-pilot's *own* Daml party. It is distinct from the AgentBank's human desk
-- and is only ever granted scoped, revocable authority via `AgentAuthorization`.
type AgentParty = Party

-- | AgentAuthorization — the on-ledger grant that bounds what the co-pilot may do.
--
-- SIGNATORY: agentBank
--   The agent bank is the sole signatory: it is the party whose authority is being
--   delegated, so only it can create (or archive) the grant. Nothing the co-pilot does
--   can manufacture this authority for itself.
-- OBSERVER: agent (the co-pilot's party)
--   The co-pilot can *see* the grant (so its service knows its scope) but cannot *alter*
--   it — it is not a signatory.
-- VISIBILITY CHECK: No borrower or lender data is carried here, and no lender is a
--   stakeholder, so this contract leaks nothing about any lender's position. The only
--   parties who can see it are the agent bank and the co-pilot it authorizes.
template AgentAuthorization
  with
    agentBank : AgentBank
    agent : AgentParty
    -- | Human-readable description of the need-to-know scope (e.g. "read covenant +
    -- borrower financials; propose drawdown settlement"). The real enforcement is the
    -- set of choices the agent party actually controls on-ledger; this field documents
    -- intent for auditors.
    scope : Text
  where
    signatory agentBank
    observer agent
    ensure scope /= ""

    -- | The agent bank can revoke the grant at any time. After this, the co-pilot's party
    -- retains only whatever authority other live contracts still give it.
    choice Revoke : ()
      controller agentBank
      do pure ()
